physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Glasgow Coma Scale score was 14/15; no focal neurological abnormality detected.
CT scan confirmed subarachnoid hemorrhage (SAH) Grade II on the World Federation of Neurosurgical Societies scale and Grade 1 on the Fisher scale.

Heavy calcification with 50% narrowing of both common carotid arteries; common femoral, external iliac, and internal iliac arteries patent bilaterally but reduced caliber; aortoiliac occlusion observed.
The treated aneurysms are stable; the untreated distal MCA aneurysm remains unchanged in size and configuration.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Untreated distal MCA aneurysm remains unchanged.
